TYLER FUQUA: Iquitos is in the Amazon basin and it's really remote compared to anywhere else in Peru.

00:02:22.920 --> 00:02:28.720
It's not accessible by road, so the only way to get there is through flying on a plane or doing it by boat

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:36.360
It has created this isolated world where a lot of the problems that we deal with can live and fester without really being addressed

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:38.800
from a socially progressive mindset.

00:02:39.160 --> 00:02:44.540
It really has allowed all the problems to persist that we are addressing on a day to day basis

00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:54.740
Las Lomas is the property and the home that we have in Iquitos. It really is a special place.

00:02:54.740 --> 00:03:02.460
It really creates a safe fun environment for kids to grow up in the childhood that's been in some ways robbed from them by their circumstances

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:11.680
A lot of our kids have different stories, but all of them have some similar themes.

00:03:11.680 --> 00:03:15.300
They've often been abused, abandoned, neglected,

00:03:15.300 --> 00:03:22.080
maybe just forgotten or uncared-for by their families or by their communities. When they come to Las Lomas,

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:27.280
they are delayed physically and emotionally, educationally.

00:03:27.460 --> 00:03:32.440
At Not Forgotten, our goal is to provide a holistic and comprehensive care for these children

00:03:32.820 --> 00:03:38.480
We want to meet their physical, educational, emotional, psychological and spiritual needs

00:03:38.480 --> 00:03:44.380
We feel like it's very important this is balanced, otherwise they're not gonna have the skills or tools they need to really

00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:50.580
be breakers of the cycles of abandonment, abuse, neglect, poverty, addiction that they came from.

00:03:51.500 --> 00:03:53.500
GENE IOLETT: We have to recover the years

00:03:54.500 --> 00:03:56.500
