00:04:03.200 --> 00:04:05.200
and the emotional support

00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:07.200
that a child should have

00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:08.420
and that our children have never had.

00:04:08.420 --> 00:04:12.040
TYLER: One of the biggest problems that we face is the brokenness of families.

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:15.260
Our goal at Not Forgotten is to try to recreate that family model.

00:04:15.500 --> 00:04:21.260
GENE: Normally, a children's home hires individuals

00:04:21.260 --> 00:04:23.000
but they don't hire a family

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.300
we hire families

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:29.600
to demonstrate a model of family to our children.

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:35.980
TYLER: That cycle of mistrust is broken through providing food, a hug, helping with homework, helping them get dressed,

00:04:36.260 --> 00:04:39.340
helping them brush their teeth, welcoming them when they get home from school.

00:04:39.340 --> 00:04:45.940
All these things are small little things, but they add up to meeting these bigger needs of what a true mother and a true father

00:04:45.940 --> 00:04:48.820
should be doing for these children, and that's something that they never had before.

00:04:49.400 --> 00:04:52.380
Not Forgotten is completely led by Peruvians,

00:04:52.380 --> 00:04:55.520
